==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palmetto flag
<hw>Pal*met"to flag</hw>. <def>Any of several flags adopted by South
Carolina after its secession. That adopted in November, 1860, had a
green cabbage palmetto in the center of a white field; the final one,
January, 1861, had a white palmetto in the center of a blue field and a
white crescent in the upper left-hand corner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palmetto State</ent>⟦br⟧
